	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001092_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Kendal</placeName> 12 Sept </p>
<lb/><p rend="right">1857 </p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>Shaw</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I mention you 
<lb/>in the preface 
<lb/>thanking you 
<lb/>&amp; <persName>Sir Roderick</persName>
<lb/>for the kind way 
<lb/>in which you 
<lb/>withheld my 
<lb/>manuscript<reg>.</reg>

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001092_0002"/><!--pb/@n='1v'--> 
<lb/>I mention <persName>Admiral 
<lb/>Smythe</persName> in the 
<lb/>body of the work<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>Sent him the 
<lb/>prefatory remarks 
<lb/>of <persName>Toynbee</persName> that 
<lb/>he might extract 
<lb/>a note as a 
<lb/>preface for 
<lb/>my table &amp; send 
<lb/>the whole on to 
<lb/>you<reg>.</reg></p>

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001092_0003"/><!--pb/@n='2r'-->
<lb/><p>Unfortunately 
<lb/>my proofs are 
<lb/>all in a box 
<lb/>we have left 
<lb/>in <placeName>England</placeName><reg>.</reg>
<lb/>I shall send 
<lb/>you what you 
<lb/>mention as 
<lb/>soon as I return 
<lb/>about the end 
<lb/>of the month<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>What part of it  do 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001092_0004"/><!--pb/@n='2v'--> 
<lb/>you wish? I fully 
<lb/>appreciate your 
<lb/>invariable kindness 
<lb/>to the end<reg>.</reg> I think 
<lb/>that last was 
<lb/>the crown of all<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>In the way I bring 
<lb/>it in you con
<lb/>trast with advantage 
<lb/>with my other 
<lb/><hi rend="underline">friends</hi><reg>.</reg> Ever 
<lb/>Yours </p>
<lb/><p>D Livingstone </p>
<lb/><p><choice><reg>L</reg><orig>l</orig></choice>eave for <placeName>Carlisle</placeName> in 3 minutes </p>
			
